<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>32-1203</num>
  <heading>Effect of leave on employment benefits or seniority.</heading>
  <text>An employee who takes leave pursuant to <cite path="§32-1202">§ 32-1202</cite> shall not lose any employment benefit or seniority accrued before or during the date of such leave.</text>
  <annotations>
    <annotation doc="D.C. Law 10-146" type="History" path="§4">Aug. 17, 1994, D.C. Law 10-146, § 4, 41 DCR 4477</annotation>
    <annotation type="Prior Codifications">1981 Ed., § 36-1603.</annotation>
  </annotations>
</section>
